# Blobolines — Cursor rules

Gooey-blob vertical-launch physics arcade game: React Three Fiber + Rapier (3D),
goo as a raymarched metaball isosurface, shipped to GitHub Pages + Android
(Capacitor). The authoritative contract is `AGENTS.md`, `STANDARDS.md`, and
`docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` — this rule is a summary.

## Hard rules

- **pnpm only.** Commands: `pnpm dev`, `pnpm build`, `pnpm test` (unit, happy-dom),
  `pnpm test:browser` (Chromium WebGL fixtures), `pnpm lint`, `pnpm typecheck`.
- **Biome** for lint+format — never ESLint/Prettier.
- **Conventional Commits**, squash-merge via PR, never commit to `main`.
- **No stubs / TODO / placeholder / "later".** Committed code works and is tested.
- **Latest-everything**; modernize past breaking changes, don't pin older.
- **Design tokens own all color** — no raw hex in `src/render/**`, `app/scene/**`,
  `app/views/**`, `src/sim/**`; use `src/styles/tokens.ts` / `tokens.css`.

## Architecture & boundaries

- `src/sim` and `src/core` are **pure**: no `three`, no React, no DOM, no
  `Math.random()` (use the seeded `Rng` from `src/core/math`). Constants live in
  `src/sim/physics/config.ts`.
- `src/render` = framework-agnostic three.js materials / goo field / VFX.
  `app/scene` = the R3F components that instantiate and drive them.
- `app/views` = DOM HUD + menus (shadcn + Motion + anime.js). UI never touches
  three objects — it goes through the `src/state` stores/bridges.
- **Never re-render per frame.** Per-frame data flows through the diagnostics /
  launch / powerup bridges in `src/state`, read inside each component's `useFrame`.

## Definition of done

`pnpm lint && pnpm typecheck && pnpm test && pnpm test:browser && pnpm build` all
green; render/UI changes carry a visual/fixture test; each touched subsystem's
`README.md` stays aligned. Verify the app RUNS, not just that tests pass.
